According to Fig. 6a, the photoelectrode is not able to generate current beyond 1.15 V versus RHE, although 1.23 V is a thermodynamical requisite for splitting water. Hence, the performance of the photoelectrode film in the photocatalytic water-splitting process was measured by determining the employed bias photon to electron conversion effectiveness (ABPE) (where bias is varied between working and counter electrodes) using the following formula52,53:7ABPE(%)=Jp×1.23-Vb×ηFPtotal×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
